"<div>\n  <h1>Roast Beef and Turkey Salad with Blackberry Vinaigrette</h1>\n  <h2>Ingredients:</h2>\n  <ul>\n    <li>2 tablespoons butter, melted</li>\n    <li>1 pound roast beef, thinly sliced</li>\n    <li>1 pound turkey, thinly sliced</li>\n    <li>1/2 cup blackberries</li>\n    <li>3 tablespoons olive oil</li>\n    <li>2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar</li>\n    <li>1 tablespoon honey</li>\n    <li>Salt and pepper, to taste</li>\n    <li>6 cups lettuce, chopped</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h2>Instructions:</h2>\n  <ol>\n    <li>Preheat the oven to 350Â°F. Brush the melted butter on both sides of the roast beef and turkey slices and season with salt and pepper.</li>\n    <li>Place the meat on a baking sheet and roast for 8-10 minutes, or until heated through.</li>\n    <li>In a small bowl, whisk together the blackberries, olive oil, balsamic vinegar, honey, salt, and pepper to make the vinaigrette.</li>\n    <li>In a large bowl, combine the lettuce, roast beef, turkey, and blackberry vinaigrette. Toss to coat evenly.</li>\n    <li>Divide the salad among 4 plates and serve.</li>\n  </ol>\n</div>"